[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/weak_twos"]
[Student "S"]
{SOUTH doesn't have much of a 3\C opening bid.

But NORTH has just the type of hand you need to bid 3NT after partner's preempt. The other three 
suits well stopped, and certain entry in Opener's long suit. Notice here that 3NT is a good contract, 
but 5\C would go down 1.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "2"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "NS"]
[Deal "E:J4.KJT963.875.42 T75.75.J643.A863 AQ63.Q82.AKQ.KQJ K982.A4.T92.T975"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "4H"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
2H pass 2NT pass 3H pass 4H pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 2, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[VersionToken "b668b1826052e2bf98e8202cad99657fd8e9d59b7b43e1f58c0fe15e6af50738"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/weak_twos"]
[Student "S"]
{When EAST opens with a Weak 2\H bid, WEST knows she will 
force to game but is thinking about slam. 

But first she needs to know if EAST has anything extra. She bids 2NT to get more information.

EAST returns to \Hs to show bare minimum so WEST settles for game.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "S"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "S:KQ9862.864.94.K6 A5.972.JT8.Q9752 JT3.AK53.AQ732.4 74.QJT.K65.AJT83"]
[Declarer "S"]
[Contract "3S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "S"]
2S pass 2NT pass 3C pass 3S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: S, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:2, nBasis: 0, nRot: 2, useStandardVul: true"]
[VersionToken "78b1ecd0e5ac525adc6a19f76993a042e9b231322792372d830f16b4bf6f32a2"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/weak_twos"]
[Student "S"]
{NORTH has one of those hands which might or might not be helpful to SOUTH. He needs 
more information about SOUTH's hand, so he bids 2NT.

SOUTH has a better than average hand, so she bids 3\C to show a high card in the suit.

NORTH was hoping for a high card in \Ds rather than \Cs, so 
he signs off in 3\S}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "4"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "All"]
[Deal "E:73.K53.KQT872.94 J982.T987.65.QT8 A64.Q42.AJ4.AK65 KQT5.AJ6.93.J732"]
[Declarer "W"]
[Contract "3NT"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
2D pass 2NT pass 3H pass 3NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 4, chOption: W, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:3, nBasis: 0, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[VersionToken "9197ee62b9ca49e529c39539295302c0d48918b5752103f35959026cb9050115"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/weak_twos"]
[Student "S"]
{With four fast winners WEST should think about game. The best approach is usually to 
use 2NT to find out more about EAST's hand.

WEST found out that EAST has good opening strength, and, most importantly, either the 
\HA or \HK. Now that she doesn't 
have to worry about the opponents taking the first five \H tricks 
she bids 3NT.}

[Event ""]
